   @{" -a   " link A} @{" -A   " link Ä} @{" -b|B " link B} @{" -c|C " link C} @{" -d   " link D} @{" -e|E " link E} @{" -f   " link F} @{" -g   " link G} @{" -h   " link H} @{" -i|I " link I}
   @{" -j|J " link J} @{" -l   " link L} @{" -n|N " link N} @{" -o   " link O} @{" -p|P " link P} @{" -q|Q " link Q} @{" -r   " link R} @{" -s|S " link S} @{" -t   " link T} @{" -u   " link U}
   @{" -v   " link V} @{" -w|W " link W} @{" -x   " link X} @{" -y|Y " link Y} @{" -z|Z " link Z}

-b	this switch enables numeric sorting
	all lines which start with a number are sorted by it and will be
	placed before all other line without numbers, if any are in the
	file.  All lines without numbers are sorted alphabetically.

	equivalent to the keyword NUMERIC/S

-B	see above
	The difference is that all lines which do not start with a number
	are erased.

@{" Contents " link MAIN} @{" << " link Ä} @{" Features " link FEATURES} @{" >> " link C}
@ENDNODE

@NODE C "sort v1.80 Documentation - Features - c|C"

   @{" -a   " link A} @{" -A   " link Ä} @{" -b|B " link B} @{" -c|C " link C} @{" -d   " link D} @{" -e|E " link E} @{" -f   " link F} @{" -g   " link G} @{" -h   " link H} @{" -i|I " link I}
   @{" -j|J " link J} @{" -l   " link L} @{" -n|N " link N} @{" -o   " link O} @{" -p|P " link P} @{" -q|Q " link Q} @{" -r   " link R} @{" -s|S " link S} @{" -t   " link T} @{" -u   " link U}
   @{" -v   " link V} @{" -w|W " link W} @{" -x   " link X} @{" -y|Y " link Y} @{" -z|Z " link Z}

-c[z,l]	with this option the number 'z' of column can be specified,
	by which the file is to be sorted. 'l' specifies, how many chars
	are used for sorting.
	This is used e.g. for sorting the RECENT files from Aminet by type.
	(-c20,10)
	If 'l' is not given, it is asked for, if 'l' given as '0' it is
	set automatical to the length of the line.
	If double lines are to be erased, comparision starts at the FIRST
	char of the lines, means the whole line is used for comparision.

	equivalent to the keyword COLSTART/K

-C[z,l]	see above
	The difference is, that the comparison for erasing double
	lines starts at the column, which is specified for sorting.
	comparision is made till end of the line, the number of chars
	for sorting doesn't have any influence.

@{" Contents " link MAIN} @{" << " link B} @{" Features " link FEATURES} @{" >> " link D}
@ENDNODE

